          %li Online Advertising

    .row.about-box-panel#panel_3
      .col-12
        %h2.section-sub-heading Graphic Designer
        %hr.clear-both
        %p.about-content
          Obsessing over clients’ brand’s identity can enlighten you to your inner weaknesses and challenge you to become better at what you love. I love to take that challenge and find new ways to be inventive using techniques to provide relevant design schemes and using color and shape to translate the emotion of a client's design. In essence, design should look and feel light and non-invasive as if you feel the section is just an exension of the whole, much like a sauce in cooking is a way to accent the main ingredients. Simple... a fantastic guiding principle.

        %ul.list-inline.about-list-tubes
          %li Branding
          %li Illustrator
          %li Photoshop
          %li Photography
          %li Logo Design

    .row.about-box-panel#panel_4
      .col-12
        %h2.section-sub-heading Web Developer
        %hr.clear-both
        %p.about-content
          Knowing the ingredients is a great place to start. But unless you can slice, dice, and your product will never have backbone. Early on, I discovered a love for the intricate details of web development (and the sadness of IE6). Pushing the CSS envelope, I moved to LESS then SASS and have the ablitiy to harness its greatness. Working on complex applications with dynamic data forces me to think on a large scale and be a master of flexible layout, thinking beyond basic, static, Photoshop layouts. Building rapid prototypes allows for quick iteration of concepts and experiences that enables immediate consumer interaction.
        %ul.list-inline.about-list-tubes
