        %h2.section-sub-heading UX Designer
        %hr.clear-both
        %p.about-content
          How'd we get here? Designing for the interaction only seemed to be the next step in customer service. Figuring out why the user does what she does is challenging and exciting. Following best practices, then throwing best practices out the window after user testing proves otherwise, is a great way to stick it to all those internet trolls. Identifing users, staying open minded about their needs  and finding common patterns in their interactions with products, allows you to develope products that will earn their trust and deliver high levels on satisfaction.
